# SLAM Presale Program (Anchor)

Solana smart contract managing the SLAM token presale. Implements tiered pricing, vesting schedules, and contribution tracking.

## Stack
- Anchor 0.31.1
- Rust (Solana BPF)
- Token-2022 (SPL Token Extension)
- Solana CLI 2.4.x

## Program ID
**Devnet**: `SLAM123...` (placeholder — deploy to get real ID)

**Note**: Program ID will change after each deployment. Update this after devnet deploy, then again for testnet/mainnet.

## Instructions

### Initialization
- `initialize` — Set up presale state (start/end times, token mint, treasury)
- `set_presale_params` — Configure rounds, pricing, allocation

### User Actions
- `contribute` — User sends SOL/USDC/USDT, receives SLAM allocation
- `claim_tokens` — Withdraw vested tokens after cliff period

### Admin Actions
- `update_round` — Adjust pricing (requires multisig)
- `emergency_pause` — Pause contributions
- `withdraw_treasury` — Move raised funds to treasury (requires multisig)

## Accounts

### PresaleState (global)
- `authority`: program deployer
- `token_mint`: SLAM mint address
- `treasury`: raised funds destination
- `start_time`, `end_time`: presale window
- `current_round`: active round index
- `total_raised`: SOL/USDC collected
- `total_slam_sold`: tokens allocated

### UserAllocation (per-user PDA)
- Seeds: `["allocation", user_pubkey]`
- `contributor`: wallet address
- `amount_contributed`: total paid
- `slam_allocated`: tokens earned
- `vesting_start`: timestamp
- `vesting_duration`: seconds
- `claimed`: amount withdrawn

### VestingSchedule (configurable)
- 25% unlock at TGE
- 75% linear vesting over 18 months (6-month cliff)

## Build Locally
```bash
cd programs/slam-presale
npm install              # Anchor + TS deps
anchor build             # Compile Rust → .so
anchor test              # Run integration tests
```

## Deploy (Devnet)
```bash
# 1. Ensure solana CLI is configured
solana config set --url devnet

# 2. Get program keypair ID
solana-keygen pubkey target/deploy/slam_presale-keypair.json

# 3. Fund deployer wallet (need ~2 SOL for devnet deploy + rent)
solana airdrop 2 <deployer-wallet>

# 4. Deploy
anchor deploy --provider.cluster devnet

# 5. Copy new program ID from output, update Anchor.toml + this README
```

